This cover pillow represents Claude Monet's famous painting: 'Wild Poppies Near Argenteuil'. Claude Monet painted The Poppy Field in 1873 on his return from the United Kingdom (in 1871) when he settled in Argenteuil with his family until 1878. It was a time that provided the artist with great fulfillment as a painter, despite the failing health of Camille his wife. This beautifully depicted summer's day and captures all its glory with the vibrant poppies complementing the wispy clouds in a clear blue sky.
